Basically what others have said: this just seems to be a stream of jokes based on different references and gags that just keep rolling past, without much between them. We've got:

- The joke of putting Disney princess stuff in SCP format and terminology (Pretty solid)

- Mixing in the anomalous world (Also good, live her version of the singing birds)

- referencing multiple Disney princesses (Funny because references?)

- In-universe genre-savvy showbiz discussions. (Iffy, several groaners).

- The Foundation are Disney villains (Hit and miss, but the  bit was really good.)

- Daevite references, violence, and gore (Funny because Incongruous? Definitely the least funny part)

Honestly, by the time I'd finished reading your containment procedures, I thought this was host gonna be Cinderella, and I was down for that. Then it got more and more complicated. The Daevite stuff is tone- killing, zaps the reader right out of the story. The stuff about people wanting to keep up with or sell the songs might be ok elsewhere, but here it was dead weight.

-1. This could be workable with a lot of trimming and some focus.





